{"id": "fx9uog", "title": "The Last Bear", "selftext": "As the lone bear stood there.. his friends and family ripped to shreds by gaping horn-gashes and printer burns.. He knew this wasn't the end.\n\nThe tattered SPY 200P lay withering on the ground next to his dead brothers.. he bends down to picks it up and knows this is not the end. The amount of blood he's spilled, that's spilled of his... He wasn't going out without glory. The fresh blood of bull-chads on his face, he remembered the last massacre like it was yesterday. Only it was weeks ago, and defeat was his whole world of late.\n\nThe shame of it had actually caused physical side effects. He lost his libido and his genitalia shrank. His desire to commune with third parties online died slowly. His entire being shriveled as he watched the bull-chads become familiar with his wife and sometimes daughter. The pain and shame of the recent memories will follow him for years, or decades. And then he lost it all.\n\nLast night his community was pillaged, leaving him no home to come back to. His friends and family were slaughtered by the Jartek tribe. This was the last straw.\n\nThere was no other choice. No other motive to do anything but this. No way to recover his shame or his pride, but this... He grabbed a second SPY 200P off a nearby beta boy, a QQQ 150p off his dead father, a TSLA 300p off his dead wife's boyfriend... AND RODE TO GLORY.\n\n&#x200B;\n\nYOU KNOW WHAT TO DO\n\n&#x200B;\n\n&#x200B;\n\nhttps://preview.redd.it/1gsyp8d6hmr41.jpg?width=1280&format=pjpg&auto=webp&s=1bf9230ce37661ca7499f5a3cd0a733f09a55657", "created_utc": 1586364096.0, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/fx9uog/the_last_bear/", "is_self": true}